WEBVTT

01:49.692 --> 01:51.611
Why, look at the time.

01:52.904 --> 01:54.072
It's almost midnight.

01:55.824 --> 01:58.076
Very nearly the witching hour.

01:59.786 --> 02:03.039
Time enough
for one more story about Sabrina,

02:04.916 --> 02:06.543
as she takes one more step

02:06.626 --> 02:09.295
towards fulfilling
the Dark Lord's Prophecy.

02:09.712 --> 02:12.882
It's a wonder anyone in Greendale
was surprised by what happened

02:12.966 --> 02:14.384
the night of the "storm."

02:15.051 --> 02:16.719
All the signs were there...

02:18.555 --> 02:20.056
if you knew where to look.

02:21.099 --> 02:24.310
-A dead bird brought in by a cat.

02:26.271 --> 02:28.523
A spilled bottle of black ink.

02:30.150 --> 02:33.153
A broken mirror in an empty room.

02:34.571 --> 02:37.782
A loaf of bread split
clean down the middle.

02:37.866 --> 02:39.159
Bloody hell.

02:39.868 --> 02:42.996
A blind woman knits
her own death shroud,

02:43.079 --> 02:44.914
aware of what's coming.

02:46.374 --> 02:47.333
Nana.

02:50.461 --> 02:52.130
It's like you predicted.

02:54.757 --> 02:56.676
I have started to see things.

02:58.094 --> 02:59.554
Impossible things.

03:02.432 --> 03:04.517
One of the things that I saw...

03:06.102 --> 03:07.812
Any sign of Tommy?

03:10.815 --> 03:13.067
I think my friend, Sabrina Spellman...

03:14.569 --> 03:15.528
is a witch.

03:16.279 --> 03:17.238
Could be.

03:18.281 --> 03:20.158
Could very well be.

03:21.326 --> 03:27.123
Nana, you said
that witches cursed us Walker women...

03:27.874 --> 03:30.001
and that's why so many of us are blind.

03:30.084 --> 03:32.045
So the story goes.

03:32.128 --> 03:35.256
Was it a Spellman who cursed our family?

03:35.340 --> 03:37.467
Oh, no, child.

03:38.051 --> 03:40.553
Don't think such dark thoughts.

03:40.637 --> 03:42.263
You know your friend.

03:42.764 --> 03:45.266
You know in your heart
if she's good or bad,

03:45.350 --> 03:49.020
and you don't need the cunning
to tell you that.

03:49.437 --> 03:50.563
The thing is...

03:52.899 --> 03:55.526
I'm not sure anymore.

03:57.695 --> 03:59.197
Just look at her...

04:00.406 --> 04:01.824
and you will know.

04:02.492 --> 04:03.826
Besides...

04:05.954 --> 04:09.749
what the cunning tells me is that...

04:10.124 --> 04:15.213
your friend is not the witch
you need to fear.

04:16.798 --> 04:19.968
The thirteen are coming, child.

04:20.677 --> 04:22.512
Like the wrath of...

04:24.305 --> 04:25.390
not God...

04:26.307 --> 04:29.477
but something near as powerful,

04:29.560 --> 04:32.355
only twisted.

04:32.855 --> 04:34.023
The thirteen?

04:34.107 --> 04:35.191
Witches.

04:36.776 --> 04:40.780
And may the Lord have mercy on our souls.

04:52.250 --> 04:53.418
Blast it!

04:54.335 --> 04:55.712
Someone's having a baby.

04:56.045 --> 04:58.673
What

04:58.756 --> 05:01.426
You know the saying.
"If a spoon falls, a baby calls."

05:03.261 --> 05:04.721
Probably Lady Blackwood's.

05:04.804 --> 05:07.598
Kindly spare me
your old wives' tales, Sister.

05:07.682 --> 05:11.102
Lady Blackwood's barely started
her fourth trimester. It'll be ages yet.

05:12.145 --> 05:13.771
Where's Sabrina

05:13.855 --> 05:15.189
In her room, I believe.

05:15.273 --> 05:16.274
Still?

05:16.649 --> 05:17.900
It's been days.

05:17.984 --> 05:19.944
Yeah, but considering
what she's been through--

05:20.028 --> 05:22.196
I know exactly
what she's been through, Ambrose.

05:22.280 --> 05:24.324
I was there to pick up the pieces,
wasn't I?

05:26.200 --> 05:28.828
She has school.
People will start to talk.

05:28.911 --> 05:33.333
Well, I've made her a little balm
for her broken heart.

05:33.416 --> 05:35.543
-I'm gonna take it up to her.
-No, I will.

05:37.295 --> 05:40.298
You can't stay in bed for the rest
of your life. You have school.

05:40.631 --> 05:42.717
What if I see him, or he sees me?

05:42.800 --> 05:44.344
It'll be too much.

05:44.427 --> 05:46.387
Your Aunt Hilda's made you a balm.

05:47.180 --> 05:48.681
To numb your heart.

05:48.765 --> 05:52.143
Rub it in your chest three times daily,
or as needed.

05:52.226 --> 05:55.646
I don't want to stop feeling.
I want to stop hurting.

05:59.317 --> 06:00.610
No, that's wrong.

06:01.944 --> 06:03.196
I want Harvey to stop hurting.

06:03.279 --> 06:06.616
There's no balm for that.
If there were, we'd be as rich as Midas.

06:07.033 --> 06:08.826
What am I gonna do, Aunt Zee?

06:11.037 --> 06:13.581
Today, you'll go to school,

06:13.664 --> 06:16.209
and you'll talk to your friends,

06:16.667 --> 06:19.879
and you'll sit in class
and answer questions.

06:21.089 --> 06:23.966
And then you'll go to the Academy.

06:24.675 --> 06:26.260
Then you'll come home...

06:26.803 --> 06:28.763
and we'll eat supper together.

06:29.514 --> 06:30.973
And then you'll go to bed.

06:31.766 --> 06:36.104
And your Aunt Hilda or I will sit
by your side until you fall asleep.

06:37.188 --> 06:38.106
And tomorrow...

06:39.232 --> 06:42.485
you'll do the same,
and it will hurt a tiny bit less.

06:43.361 --> 06:45.988
And the next day, it will hurt even less.

06:46.364 --> 06:48.449
After what I put Harvey through...

06:50.201 --> 06:52.078
how can I ever face him again?

06:52.537 --> 06:53.496
You...

06:56.707 --> 06:58.000
I'm not sure.

06:59.794 --> 07:01.379
I've never been where you are.

07:11.097 --> 07:13.599
Perhaps you just do, Sabrina.

07:14.350 --> 07:16.936
As bravely and as humbly as you can.

07:48.134 --> 07:49.343
-Sabrina.
-Sabrina.

07:49.635 --> 07:51.012
Roz. Susie.

07:51.804 --> 07:52.722
What's going on?

07:53.306 --> 07:54.765
What's going on with you?

07:54.849 --> 07:57.143
Yeah, you look
a little freaked out, Sabrina.

07:58.311 --> 07:59.812
I called you all weekend.

08:00.104 --> 08:00.980
Me, too.

08:01.564 --> 08:04.150
I wasn't, uh, feeling that great.

08:08.779 --> 08:09.780
'Brina, we want...

08:10.781 --> 08:12.283
-We need to ask you--
-Are you a witch?

08:23.044 --> 08:24.003
What?

08:25.463 --> 08:28.925
You guys, if this is some kind of joke?

08:29.008 --> 08:30.259
It's not a joke.

08:31.469 --> 08:33.095
The cunning showed me something.

08:34.055 --> 08:35.181
A vision.

08:36.057 --> 08:38.726
And... my Aunt Dorothea...

08:40.186 --> 08:41.854
wrote about you in her journals.

08:41.938 --> 08:44.357
She said the Spellmans were
a family of witches.

08:44.899 --> 08:46.108
That's just...

08:48.361 --> 08:49.445
That's just...

08:49.737 --> 08:50.863
'Brina?

08:52.657 --> 08:57.495
I wanted to tell youÂ so many times, but...

08:58.788 --> 09:00.206
but how could I?

09:00.748 --> 09:04.085
-And now Harvey knows. Everything is--
-Harvey knows?

09:04.168 --> 09:05.211
It's over.

09:06.629 --> 09:08.548
-He broke up with me.
-What

09:08.631 --> 09:11.050
Because of everything.

09:11.384 --> 09:12.510
All the lying.

09:12.802 --> 09:16.597
I've been hiding this whole other life,
going to this different school.

09:16.681 --> 09:17.598
What do you mean?

09:17.682 --> 09:21.602
For witches.
But I'm still the same person.

09:23.187 --> 09:24.772
Even after what happened with Tommy.

09:24.855 --> 09:26.774
-Sabrina?
-I did it.

09:28.109 --> 09:29.694
I resurrected Tommy.

09:30.403 --> 09:31.862
I wanted to help.

09:31.946 --> 09:35.283
But then he came back all wrong, and...

09:35.741 --> 09:38.786
it's all my fault, and Harvey...

09:39.412 --> 09:41.747
Harvey had to kill him.

09:41.831 --> 09:42.790
-Oh, my.
-Oh.

09:42.873 --> 09:44.000
Sabrina...

09:46.127 --> 09:49.130
I mean, he'll never forgive me.
I mean, how could he?

09:49.213 --> 09:50.590
I'm so sorry.

09:51.757 --> 09:55.553
I never wanted to lie to you or hurt you.
Any of you.

09:55.636 --> 09:57.722
-That's all I've been doing.
-That's okay.

09:58.264 --> 09:59.223
It's okay.

10:00.683 --> 10:03.769
-We're here for you, Sabrina.
-We will always be here for you.

10:03.853 --> 10:06.731
Thank you, guys. You're the best.

10:07.732 --> 10:11.360
I can't tell you
how disappointed I was to hear

10:11.736 --> 10:15.239
Sabrina's mortal friends rally around her.

10:15.323 --> 10:17.491
Despite my every manipulation,

10:17.575 --> 10:20.494
despite everything they'd learned
about Sabrina,

10:20.578 --> 10:23.331
her friends would not be cleaved from her.

10:24.248 --> 10:27.084
The Dark Lord was growing
impatient with me.

10:27.627 --> 10:29.670
I needed to change tactics.

10:29.754 --> 10:32.798
Introduce a threat to Greendale

10:32.882 --> 10:36.510
that would compel Sabrina
to make certain choices

10:36.594 --> 10:38.012
that would, in turn...

10:40.723 --> 10:42.975
...force her to separate from them.

10:43.351 --> 10:44.894
As for the threat, I...

10:46.145 --> 10:47.730
had an idea or two...

10:49.940 --> 10:51.651
or thirteen...

10:53.277 --> 10:56.906
...buried right under our noses.

10:57.990 --> 11:02.536
But I would have to wait
until midnight, the witching hour.

11:03.579 --> 11:05.665
And I would need a warm body.

11:06.499 --> 11:07.792
There you go.

11:17.468 --> 11:19.095
-Sabrina?

11:19.178 --> 11:21.013
I just wanted to say I'm sorry

11:21.097 --> 11:23.099
for how everything went down
with the resurrection.

11:23.182 --> 11:24.183
How did you hear?

11:24.684 --> 11:26.060
Bad news travels fast.

11:26.143 --> 11:27.853
It's all anybody's talking about.

11:28.729 --> 11:30.064
Your failed resurrection.

11:30.481 --> 11:31.691
Thoughts and prayers.

11:32.316 --> 11:34.110
Isn't that how the mortals put it?

11:38.989 --> 11:40.324
How is the mortal?

11:41.200 --> 11:44.453
His name is Harvey, and he is devastated.

11:45.663 --> 11:46.789
We broke up.

11:47.331 --> 11:49.041
You really love him, don't you?

11:50.668 --> 11:52.795
That's the one thing I envy about mortals.

11:53.963 --> 11:56.006
The way they can give themselves
to each other.

11:57.007 --> 12:00.261
Witches are aces
at passion and lust, but...

12:01.011 --> 12:02.221
when it comes to love...

12:03.514 --> 12:04.515
true love...

12:06.642 --> 12:07.852
not so much.

12:08.269 --> 12:09.353
Why is that?

12:10.521 --> 12:12.606
Our Dark Lord is a jealous lord.

12:13.023 --> 12:15.484
He wants us to love him and only him.

12:15.568 --> 12:17.027
Selfish, isn't it?

12:17.862 --> 12:20.156
Yeah, but it would be easier in some ways.

12:20.239 --> 12:21.073
Nah.

12:22.032 --> 12:23.743
I'd trade all the witch-orgies
in the world

12:23.826 --> 12:25.369
for what you and the mortal have.

12:25.453 --> 12:26.495
Had.

12:27.413 --> 12:29.081
You'll pull through this, Sabrina.

12:30.666 --> 12:32.626
And if you need a shoulder to cry on...

12:38.507 --> 12:39.717
That can't be good.

12:53.898 --> 12:56.192
Steve. Stevie, slow down.

12:56.275 --> 12:59.528
Hey, you asked me out, remember?
You suggested we come out to the woods.

12:59.612 --> 13:01.238
That's true.

13:01.322 --> 13:03.282
So stop playing hard to get.

13:03.365 --> 13:06.202
Why are you virgins always so aggressive?

13:07.119 --> 13:10.539
-What? I'm not a--
-Oh, Mr. Loomis.

13:10.915 --> 13:15.211
I smell virgins
the way a rabid dog smells blood.

13:17.630 --> 13:19.048
But don't be embarrassed.

13:20.299 --> 13:22.885
A virgin suits my needs tonight.

13:23.511 --> 13:26.013
I call out to the Greendale Thirteen!

13:26.388 --> 13:29.266
To the witches hunted by mortals!

13:30.142 --> 13:32.520
Betrayed by their own kind.

13:32.603 --> 13:35.147
Hung from this tree by their necks.

13:35.231 --> 13:38.567
Arise, Sisters. Arise.

13:49.203 --> 13:50.704
Welcome back, ladies.

13:51.872 --> 13:54.208
Where are we?

13:54.625 --> 13:55.751
Greendale.

13:57.169 --> 13:59.421
And the witching hour is upon us.

14:00.756 --> 14:06.846
Tonight and tomorrow,
for one hour, from midnight to one,

14:08.472 --> 14:11.100
you may walk the earth again...

14:12.059 --> 14:13.936
to claim your revenge.

14:14.895 --> 14:16.856
Go forth, Sisters.

14:17.481 --> 14:20.192
Take to the sleeping streets.

14:21.068 --> 14:25.322
Reacquaint yourself
with the town you so despise.

14:27.741 --> 14:29.660
And then summon the butcher...

14:30.578 --> 14:33.664
who will end Greendale, once...

14:34.790 --> 14:36.083
and for all.

14:55.144 --> 14:57.771
-Out of my way.
-Madame...

14:57.855 --> 14:58.939
Thank you.

15:01.775 --> 15:02.610
Hilda?

15:03.193 --> 15:04.403
Do you feel that?

15:06.822 --> 15:09.366
It's like a train going past a graveyard.

15:32.890 --> 15:33.891
Who's there?

15:37.645 --> 15:38.771
Show yourself.

15:41.899 --> 15:44.193
I said, show yourself!

16:00.709 --> 16:02.127
Wake up, Susie.

16:14.348 --> 16:15.516
What the hell?

16:16.016 --> 16:17.309
They've come back.

16:19.353 --> 16:20.813
Who has, Aunt Dorothea?

16:21.230 --> 16:24.441
The thirteen women,
hung to death as witches.

16:24.900 --> 16:27.611
Women I brought to the New World
to live freely.

16:28.195 --> 16:31.657
The same women I buried here on our land.

16:31.740 --> 16:33.158
On our farm?

16:33.826 --> 16:37.329
No one else would cut them down
from the hanging tree in the woods.

16:37.413 --> 16:39.456
They deserved a place to rest.

16:40.416 --> 16:41.625
Why are they back?

16:41.709 --> 16:44.420
They were hunted and betrayed.

16:45.087 --> 16:47.631
They should've been buried
by their own kind.

16:47.965 --> 16:49.633
Among their own kind.

16:50.634 --> 16:51.927
Wrathful.

16:53.012 --> 16:54.596
They come for vengeance.

16:54.680 --> 16:56.140
Is there any way to stop them?

17:06.025 --> 17:08.569
We don't have to tramp
out into the woodsÂ after midnight

17:08.652 --> 17:11.488
-just to get kinky.
-Ssh! That's not what this is.

17:11.572 --> 17:14.366
I just want to show youÂ my favorite spot.

17:14.450 --> 17:17.786
I already know your favorite spot,
and it's right between your--

17:17.870 --> 17:20.456
Favorite spot for moon-gazing, you ass.

17:22.166 --> 17:23.208
Ambrose, what?

17:23.876 --> 17:25.753
What's going on

17:31.884 --> 17:32.926
What is that?

17:34.428 --> 17:35.721
Over there. Look.

17:41.602 --> 17:43.145
It's a circle of witches.

17:43.228 --> 17:44.646
From our coven?

17:44.730 --> 17:45.981
Gathering for what?

17:47.357 --> 17:48.317
Sounds like...

17:50.402 --> 17:51.403
a summoning spell.

17:51.862 --> 17:54.239
They're calling forth something.
Ambrose, we should go.

17:54.323 --> 17:56.867
Why? If they're witches,
they're our people.

17:57.284 --> 17:58.994
They're probably out here
having a good time.

18:00.329 --> 18:01.872
And what if they're not?

18:42.830 --> 18:44.123
Warlock...

18:46.667 --> 18:49.878
Take this warning to your masters
at the Church of Night.

18:54.299 --> 18:55.968
It's okay, I promise.

18:57.886 --> 18:59.805
Tommy, stop it! Tommy!

19:20.242 --> 19:21.076
Hi.

19:24.955 --> 19:25.831
Hi.

19:26.957 --> 19:28.625
How are you, Harvey?

19:29.042 --> 19:30.460
Better than my dad.

19:31.336 --> 19:32.713
What did you tell him?

19:33.255 --> 19:34.464
That Tommy did it.

19:35.716 --> 19:37.509
To put himself out of his misery.

19:37.926 --> 19:40.637
He just nodded and said,
"He was my Tommy."

19:41.847 --> 19:46.643
Then we called the funeral home,
but not you guys, the one in Riverdale.

19:47.644 --> 19:48.812
That makes sense.

19:49.479 --> 19:50.314
Yeah.

19:50.731 --> 19:53.317
I've been thinking about you nonstop,
Harvey.

19:53.775 --> 19:58.739
I've wanted to call you so badly,
but I just thought that I shouldn't--

19:58.822 --> 20:00.324
You know, it's funny...

20:01.909 --> 20:03.327
knowing now that you're a...

20:04.244 --> 20:07.206
a witch makes a lot of sense somehow.

20:07.289 --> 20:09.708
There's so many things
I never understood before.

20:10.709 --> 20:11.752
About you...

20:13.378 --> 20:14.296
about us.

20:14.796 --> 20:17.132
I thought maybe
I was just too stupid to understand.

20:17.216 --> 20:18.175
No.

20:18.550 --> 20:22.012
Harvey, it kills me
that you ever felt that way.

20:22.095 --> 20:25.182
I just couldn't tell you before.

20:25.766 --> 20:27.351
I should've trusted you.

20:28.060 --> 20:29.144
I know that now.

20:31.688 --> 20:33.273
You must really hate me.

20:34.608 --> 20:36.193
I could never hate you.

20:36.860 --> 20:37.819
Remember...

20:39.196 --> 20:41.073
I promised you that on your birthday.

20:46.745 --> 20:50.540
But every time I look at you,
all I can think about is my brother.

20:56.213 --> 20:58.966
Hi. So sorry to interrupt.

20:59.049 --> 21:02.135
Harvey, I'm so sorry
about your poor brother.

21:02.219 --> 21:05.514
-Uh, thanks, Miss Spellman.
-What's going on, Aunt Hilda?

21:05.597 --> 21:09.685
So, you need to come
to the Church of Night straight away.

21:09.768 --> 21:12.187
Father Blackwood has called
an emergency meeting.

21:12.271 --> 21:13.105
During the day?

21:13.188 --> 21:16.900
Hm-mm. Bit of a crisis,
so if you could meet me there.

21:16.984 --> 21:18.193
So sorry.

21:27.077 --> 21:29.621
Your aunt, she wasn't really here,
was she?

21:29.913 --> 21:34.001
No, she was... astral-projecting.

21:34.084 --> 21:35.794
And the Church of Night?

21:36.586 --> 21:37.671
Is our coven.

21:37.754 --> 21:38.755
Right.

21:40.257 --> 21:43.010
Well, it sounds like
you'd better get going.

21:43.093 --> 21:45.345
-Harvey...
-I mean, you have to.

21:46.972 --> 21:48.098
It's your coven.

21:51.685 --> 21:52.644
Yeah.

21:59.234 --> 22:00.902
But I hope we can talk some more.

22:02.863 --> 22:03.905
When you're ready.

22:09.828 --> 22:11.163
Brothers and Sisters...

22:11.955 --> 22:14.166
last night I witnessed an omen.

22:15.125 --> 22:16.752
As so many of you did.

22:17.127 --> 22:20.630
A horrifying sign
that can portend only one thing.

22:21.173 --> 22:24.634
The Fires of the Abyss
are being made ready.

22:25.093 --> 22:28.263
The Pit is yawning beneath us.

22:29.056 --> 22:33.935
The Dark Lord has seen
our contemptible weakness.

22:34.978 --> 22:39.441
Our blatant disregard
for witch law and doctrine.

22:40.484 --> 22:43.820
And Satan,
vengeful God that he is, plans...

22:43.904 --> 22:45.155
...to punish us!

22:45.697 --> 22:46.698
Father Blackwood!

22:48.200 --> 22:50.869
It is not the Dark Lord's wrath
that has come for us,

22:50.952 --> 22:53.705
it is... the Greendale Thirteen.

22:53.789 --> 22:55.749
We stumbled upon them
in the woods last night.

22:55.832 --> 22:58.251
They were performing some kind of ritual.

22:58.335 --> 22:59.795
A summoning spell.

22:59.878 --> 23:02.214
They bore into our minds. Bewitched us.

23:02.589 --> 23:05.217
We're only alive because they wanted
us to deliver a message.

23:05.300 --> 23:07.552
What message? Spit it out.

23:07.636 --> 23:10.222
They've returned to visit Death
upon the town of Greendale.

23:10.639 --> 23:14.059
Last night, they rose to call forth
their Crimson Avenger.

23:14.351 --> 23:17.437
Tonight, on the witching hour, he rides!

23:17.521 --> 23:20.607
Who rides, Ambrose

23:22.692 --> 23:24.861
The Red Angel of Death, Auntie.

23:24.945 --> 23:28.698
The Thirteen will knock down
all the doors in town for him,

23:29.074 --> 23:30.200
and in his wake,

23:31.201 --> 23:35.831
the firstborn of Greendale,
both mortal and witch alike, will perish!

23:39.251 --> 23:41.211
Silence! Silence!

23:43.797 --> 23:45.924
You've done well to bring this to us,
Brother Ambrose,

23:46.007 --> 23:50.429
but if it is the wrath of the Thirteen and
their messenger of Crimson Death we face,

23:50.804 --> 23:56.143
I, your High Priest, will protect you.

23:57.561 --> 24:01.440
With all due respect, Your Excellency,
and acknowledging

24:01.523 --> 24:04.276
that I'm excommunicated, protect us how?

24:05.068 --> 24:08.155
The coven will gather
within the walls of the Academy.

24:08.238 --> 24:12.492
Fortified, bound
by our combinedÂ impenetrable magics,

24:12.576 --> 24:15.203
we will stand together,

24:15.287 --> 24:19.624
until the blood-red horseman
has passed through Greendale!

24:25.046 --> 24:26.590
But what about the mortals?

24:27.632 --> 24:29.259
The people of Greendale.

24:31.470 --> 24:34.723
Let them run to their False God
and gnash their teeth and wail,

24:34.806 --> 24:35.807
or whatever it is they do.

24:36.433 --> 24:40.061
Brethren, be inside the Academy
by midnight...

24:40.562 --> 24:42.272
or face the Thirteen...

24:43.273 --> 24:45.817
and their avenging angel alone.

24:47.110 --> 24:48.445
I don't understand.

24:48.528 --> 24:51.239
Why would the Greendale Thirteen
be angryÂ at us?

24:51.323 --> 24:54.242
It's a bloody mess
what happened to the Greendale Thirteen.

24:54.326 --> 24:56.870
The most ignoble chapter
of the Church of Night's history,

24:56.953 --> 24:59.873
but it is our history,
and we cannot deny it.

24:59.956 --> 25:02.334
After the witch trials of Salem,
all the witches

25:02.417 --> 25:04.044
in this part of the country
were terrified.

25:04.127 --> 25:06.505
Trouble was brewing in Greendale,

25:06.588 --> 25:09.966
and people... mortals were identifying
and arresting witches,

25:10.050 --> 25:12.093
including the original Thirteen.

25:12.928 --> 25:17.807
And while they sat in their cell,
the other witches met and decided--

25:17.891 --> 25:19.893
The Thirteen would be sacrificed.

25:20.560 --> 25:22.979
To appease the mortals' blood-lust.

25:25.023 --> 25:28.068
While those thirteen women were tortured
and hung,

25:28.151 --> 25:29.486
the rest of the witches...

25:30.820 --> 25:33.323
burned their poppets
and buried their cauldrons.

25:33.406 --> 25:36.409
They were scapegoats
to quell the rising witch hysteria.

25:36.493 --> 25:39.579
The coven could have come together
to save the Thirteen, but they...

25:40.664 --> 25:43.375
We, our ancestors...

25:44.834 --> 25:46.545
decided not to risk it.

25:47.712 --> 25:51.424
So we're all descendants of the witches
who turned their backs on the Thirteen

25:51.508 --> 25:54.553
and let them die? No wonder they hate us.

25:54.636 --> 25:58.348
And the mortals that did the actual
hunting and hanging,Â to be fair.

25:58.431 --> 26:01.101
Well, you'd better believe
that I am not abandoning my friends

26:01.184 --> 26:03.687
to go hide
in some magical doomsday bunker.

26:03.770 --> 26:06.690
And before you even try
to stop me, Auntie Zee--

26:06.773 --> 26:10.068
On the contrary, I think we should
all stay and protect the town.

26:10.151 --> 26:11.653
-Really?
-I didn't expect that.

26:11.736 --> 26:14.990
And why not?
The Greendale Thirteen were sacrificed

26:15.073 --> 26:17.534
so that the pack might survive.

26:17.826 --> 26:21.204
But we need not make
the same mistake again.

26:21.663 --> 26:23.415
We are Spellmans.

26:23.832 --> 26:26.001
That means we stand tall, with dignity,

26:26.084 --> 26:28.044
and we do what is right.

26:28.837 --> 26:30.839
As your father always did, Sabrina.

26:31.298 --> 26:35.385
The mortals may be weak,
but they do not deserve this grim fate.

26:35.802 --> 26:40.432
Doom has been unleashed by witches.
It must be averted by witches.

26:40.515 --> 26:42.934
All right, but protect them how?

26:43.268 --> 26:46.438
We can hardly be all places at once.

26:46.521 --> 26:48.148
We can't protect the whole town.

26:48.231 --> 26:51.359
We can if we do the same
as Father Blackwood is doing.

26:51.443 --> 26:53.153
We gather the mortals together.

26:53.236 --> 26:55.905
Zelda, I think I might have the answer.

26:56.364 --> 27:00.285
Dr. Cerberus told me something.
He used to be the local weatherman.

27:00.368 --> 27:02.287
-Oh, for Satan's sake!
-Um...

27:02.370 --> 27:05.540
He said that in the event of a tornado
or severe weather,

27:05.624 --> 27:09.586
that the town's designated shelter was
Baxter High basement.

27:09.669 --> 27:11.671
That's a great idea, Aunt Hilda.

27:12.547 --> 27:13.798
All we need is a tornado.

27:14.466 --> 27:16.635
That's easy enough.

27:27.520 --> 27:30.649
Boreas, North Wind, I summon you.

27:31.191 --> 27:34.819
Euros, East Wind, I summon you.

27:34.903 --> 27:38.031
Notos, South Wind, I summon you.

27:38.114 --> 27:41.993
Zephuros, West Wind, I summon you.

27:50.585 --> 27:52.629
Is it working

27:53.171 --> 27:54.381
Give it a moment.

28:23.493 --> 28:25.870
Pray to Satan the mortals
heed the warning.

28:26.621 --> 28:28.915
And for the most part, they did.

28:29.416 --> 28:31.501
The mortals of Greendale gathered

28:31.584 --> 28:34.212
to take refuge
in the bowels of Baxter High.

28:37.424 --> 28:41.261
All right. All right.
Easy does it. Nice and slow.

28:41.553 --> 28:45.306
That's it. There's plenty of room
for all in the storm shelter.

28:45.390 --> 28:48.059
Don't you find this invigorating,
Ms. Wardwell?

28:48.560 --> 28:51.730
I've always been fascinated
by tornadoes myself,

28:51.813 --> 28:53.565
ever since The Wizard of Oz.

28:54.816 --> 28:55.942
And now, here we are.

28:56.025 --> 28:59.195
Our school, the only safe place
in Greendale.

28:59.863 --> 29:01.489
I'm engorged with excitement.

29:01.573 --> 29:02.615
Mr. Hawthorne--

29:02.699 --> 29:06.661
Perhaps, when all this is over,
you and I might finally have that drink?

29:15.253 --> 29:16.463
Father Blackwood?

29:17.589 --> 29:19.591
-All are accounted for.
-Splendid.

29:20.091 --> 29:21.301
With our collective energies,

29:21.384 --> 29:23.470
we shall prevent the witches
or their Red Angel

29:23.553 --> 29:25.138
from crossing our threshold.

29:25.221 --> 29:26.681
All save the Spellmans.

29:27.265 --> 29:28.516
None of them are here.

29:29.309 --> 29:30.477
Not even Ambrose.

29:33.104 --> 29:33.938
Pity.

29:34.397 --> 29:35.940
I had hopes for that boy.

29:36.357 --> 29:37.233
Never mind.

29:38.985 --> 29:40.487
He made his choice.

29:53.625 --> 29:55.210
Susie, have you seen Harvey?

29:55.293 --> 29:58.379
No, and I saw Roz's dad,
but I don't think Roz is here, Sabrina.

29:58.463 --> 30:00.173
-I'll go to Harvey's.
-I'll go to Roz's.

30:00.256 --> 30:03.218
But, Susie, you have to be back
before midnight.

30:05.804 --> 30:08.139
Why aren't you at school

30:08.223 --> 30:11.810
I did, but we've got a storm cellar,
and my dad's in no shape to travel,

30:11.893 --> 30:13.770
-so we're gonna stay here.
-Harvey, you can't.

30:13.853 --> 30:18.233
It's not a tornado that's coming,
it's something much, much worse.

30:19.108 --> 30:20.151
You must mean witches.

30:20.235 --> 30:22.987
Yes, and then something called
the Red Angel of Death.

30:23.071 --> 30:24.739
-But we can protect you.
-You?

30:25.782 --> 30:28.159
Witches will protect me
and my dad from other witches?

30:30.286 --> 30:33.665
That's okay. I appreciate the offer,
but I'll protect myself.

30:34.207 --> 30:36.209
I'll protect my dad,
and I'll protect this house.

30:36.292 --> 30:38.795
-Harvey, now is not the time--
-It's what Tommy would've done.

30:39.379 --> 30:42.590
You've gotta understand why I don't want
to rely on witches for my protection now.

30:42.674 --> 30:45.260
-No, I know--
-Please don't fight me on this, 'Brina.

30:46.928 --> 30:48.638
I said, I'm staying.

30:49.931 --> 30:51.224
I'm done being a coward.

31:00.316 --> 31:05.071
My Nana Ruth doesn't want to go,
and I can't leave her alone.

31:05.154 --> 31:08.950
But everyone's at the school, Roz.
There's a tornado coming.

31:09.033 --> 31:10.368
Child, please.

31:10.827 --> 31:12.412
We're Walker women.

31:12.787 --> 31:13.955
We're cunning women.

31:14.038 --> 31:17.667
We know what's coming,
and it ain't a tornado.

31:19.586 --> 31:21.087
It's witches, Susie.

31:21.796 --> 31:25.592
And... a man dressed in red
on a white horse.

31:25.675 --> 31:28.177
Even more reason for you to be
at Baxter High with the rest of us.

31:28.261 --> 31:29.679
Listen here, young man.

31:30.263 --> 31:33.975
I have spent the better part of 30 years
sitting in this chair.

31:34.350 --> 31:37.020
I don't see any reason to leave now.

31:37.812 --> 31:38.646
Roz?

31:41.274 --> 31:42.525
I'm sorry, Susie.

31:46.362 --> 31:47.572
Then I'm staying, too.

31:47.780 --> 31:48.615
Susie.

31:48.698 --> 31:50.241
I'm staying, Roz.

31:50.700 --> 31:52.201
It's what Dorothea would do.

31:52.994 --> 31:54.996
It's what she would want me to do.

31:55.371 --> 31:56.289
I know it.

32:00.585 --> 32:02.128
Sabrina, where have you been?

32:02.211 --> 32:05.048
The mortals are down in the shelter,
and it's almost the witching hour.

32:05.131 --> 32:08.718
I went to Harvey's, and then I had
to make a detour to call in a favor.

32:08.801 --> 32:09.928
A favor

32:13.222 --> 32:14.599
Hey. Harvey, right?

32:15.016 --> 32:16.643
-Yeah. Who are you?
-I'm Nick Scratch.

32:16.726 --> 32:19.520
Sabrina sent me. I'm a friend of hers
and your back-up for the night.

32:20.146 --> 32:22.649
So I'll need you to show me every window
and door in this house,

32:22.732 --> 32:24.567
so I can seal and bind them for you.

32:28.112 --> 32:29.364
